<div id="review_19746590" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/19746590" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/992140-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1385104970p2/992140.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/19746590?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/992140-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer19746590&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer19746590" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12058825419624514458">This was a cliche feel-good book. It only took a day to read and it had a nice message. That being said, it&apos;s not great literature and is entirely forgettable. I didn&apos;t identify with the main characters and I don&apos;t really like books in which rape plays a large part of the plot. As far as a love story between the deceased parents, it was very sweet and satisfying. Having the family pastor turn out to be the rapist and suprise father was a bit much for me. I just don&apos;t think I could ever have my p</span>
  <span id="freeText12058825419624514458" style="display:none">This was a cliche feel-good book. It only took a day to read and it had a nice message. That being said, it's not great literature and is entirely forgettable. I didn't identify with the main characters and I don't really like books in which rape plays a large part of the plot. As far as a love story between the deceased parents, it was very sweet and satisfying. Having the family pastor turn out to be the rapist and suprise father was a bit much for me. I just don't think I could ever have my pastor be a man who once raped me (even if he was high at the time), and was the secret father to my child. Forgiveness is real and true, but the consequences of sin, particularly rape, are also real and true. I feel I could forgive such an act through God's help, but that man would not ever become my own and my family's spiritual advisor. What husband would go to his wife's rapist for spiritual guidance? Two thumbs down.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12058825419624514458" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


